# Governance Frameworks
SECTION 1: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
Perplexity Enterprise Pro is the organization's officially adopted AI-powered research and answer platform, licensed for enterprise-wide use across all full-time employees, contractors, and part-time staff. The platform combines real-time web retrieval with internal organizational document search across connected repositories including SharePoint, Google Drive, and OneDrive, delivering citation-backed answers through a multi-model architecture that dynamically routes queries across GPT-5.2, Claude Sonnet, Gemini, and Perplexity's proprietary Sonar model. Every response is grounded in retrieved content and accompanied by numbered citations, making outputs traceable and verifiable rather than generated from a static training dataset. The platform is accessible via web browser, desktop application, and mobile application and authenticates through the organization's existing identity provider via SAML 2.0 single sign-on.

The organization is adopting Perplexity Enterprise Pro to consolidate fragmented information retrieval into a single governed interface, eliminate Shadow AI Use on ungoverned consumer platforms, and deliver AI-assisted productivity gains across all functions under a governance structure that addresses Hallucination, Data Leakage / PII Exposure, Least Privilege Violation, Prompt Injection, Uncontrolled Agentic Execution, Unauthorized Data Retention, HIPAA Non-Compliance, EU AI Act Violation, Zero Data Retention Breach, Vendor Lock-In, and Hallucinated Output Distribution. The platform has been assessed through a full Risk Assessment and AI Control Library developed by the Office of AI Governance and is recommended for Conditional Approval pending completion of all required pre-deployment controls.

SECTION 2: GOVERNANCE STRUCTURE (RACI)
The following RACI documents accountability for governing Perplexity Enterprise Pro across the organization. R = Responsible, A = Accountable, C = Consulted, I = Informed.
Business Owner
Accountable for the strategic decision to adopt and maintain Perplexity Enterprise Pro. Owns the business justification for the platform. Approves the platform for enterprise use. Reviews and reaffirms the Model Card annually. Serves as the executive escalation point for governance decisions. Informed of all High probability risk events including Hallucination / Uncontrolled Agentic Execution and Shadow AI Use / Insufficient Governance Onboarding. Receives quarterly adoption and monitoring reports.
RACI: Accountable
AI Governance Lead, Office of AI Governance
Responsible for all governance documentation including the Platform Assessment, Risk Assessment, AI Control Library, Model Card, Acceptable Use Policy, and this Governance Framework. Authors, maintains, and enforces governance controls across all user populations including FTEs, contractors, and part-time staff. Conducts semi-annual governance reviews. Reviews audit logs quarterly in coordination with IT Security. Categorizes and escalates all AI-related incidents by named risk. Serves as the primary point of contact for auditors, regulators, and legal counsel.
RACI: Responsible
IT Security Administrator
Responsible for implementing and maintaining all technical security controls including SSO and MFA enforcement, least privilege provisioning, SCIM-based deprovisioning, Security Hub configuration, model enablement restrictions, audit log capture, and connector permission management. Conducts formal quarterly audit log reviews. Escalates Least Privilege Violation, Prompt Injection, Data Leakage, and Uncontrolled Agentic Execution events to Legal and executive leadership within 48 hours.
RACI: Responsible / Consulted
Privacy and Legal
Consulted on all data handling decisions including Data Leakage / PII Exposure controls, HIPAA Non-Compliance risk mitigation, EU AI Act Violation obligations, and Zero Data Retention Breach protections. Responsible for confirming and executing the Business Associate Agreement before any PHI-adjacent use is authorized. Reviews and confirms the Data Processing Agreement and Zero Data Retention policy at contract execution and annual renewal. Escalation point for all regulatory exposure events.
RACI: Consulted / Responsible for legal instruments
Platform Owner / IT Administrator
Responsible for day-to-day platform administration including user provisioning, connector configuration, Security Hub settings management, and LMS training tracking. Implements technical controls as directed by the AI Governance Lead and IT Security Administrator. Manages the access provisioning workflow ensuring AUP acknowledgment and training completion are enforced as hard prerequisites before any access is granted.
RACI: Responsible
Department Heads and Managers
Accountable for enforcing AUP compliance within their teams. Responsible for communicating citation verification requirements for Hallucination mitigation, organizational approval requirements for Hallucinated Output Distribution prevention, and user confirmation requirements for Uncontrolled Agentic Execution prevention to all direct reports. Receive quarterly governance check-in summaries. Escalate suspected misuse or AI-related incidents to IT and the AI Governance Lead immediately.
RACI: Accountable at department level / Informed
End Users: FTEs, Contractors, and Part-Time Staff
Responsible for complying with the AUP, completing required governance training before platform access is granted, verifying citations before acting on any output to mitigate Hallucination risk, confirming action scope before any agentic execution, and reporting suspected AI-related incidents to IT immediately. Individually accountable for the accuracy of all work product incorporating Perplexity outputs.
RACI: Responsible for individual compliance
